SOURCE_ID.Definition: Source Identification of feature.  This is generally the GC ID but also may also include other contributor ID naming conventions.

SRC_DATE.Definition: Date of source imagery (YYYYMMDD) for the feature

INFORM.Definition: Ancillary Information (e.g. Describing or defining a feature)

Domain: Natural.Great Lake Or Lake Or Pond
Natural.Great Lake Or Lake Or Pond.Approximate

VER_DATE.Definition: Date of verification imagery (YYYYMMDD) for the feature

SRC_RESOLU.Definition: Resolution of source (imagery or grid) in meters used for compiling shoreline

DATA_SOURC.Definition: Data Source describing the type of imagery used in compilation

EXT_METH.Definition: Method used to extract feature from source

DAT_SET_CR.Definition: Data Set Credit of original compiled shoreline

FIPS_ALPHA.Definition: two- letter FIPS State Alpha Code for each State and the District of Columbia. The FIPS State Alpha Code is identical to the two-letter U.S. Postal Service (USPS) abbreviation for each entity. Areas not included in the FIPS State Alpha Code are identified as "99".
